dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 colored images from 10 classes, with each image sized 32x32 pixels. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 colored images from 100 classes, with each image sized 32x32 pixels. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Jiayu Wu
Qixiang Zhang

dcterms:description: A dataset containing 110,000 colored images from 200 classes, with each image sized 64x64 pixels. It is a smaller version of the ImageNet dataset and is used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Tiny ImageNet
